User Stories - Requirements - Features

## ADMIN USER - Manage Users

- [ ] **Users list**: Dynamic list of users to manage.
- [ ] **Filter users**: Filter by email or username.
- [ ] **Change roles**: Promote unsigned → regular or admin.
- [ ] **Block users**: Temporarily suspend or block users for bad behavior.
- [ ] **Unblock users**: Restore access for previously blocked users.
- [ ] **Manage reported content**: Admin can review and remove inappropriate photos/comments.

## ADMIN USER - Manage Categories

- [ ] **Categories list**: Dynamic categories management.
- [ ] **Add category**: Admin can add categories.
- [ ] **Edit category**: Admin can rename categories.

## ADMIN USER - Settings of the Notifications

- [ ] **Notification options**: Configure types and delivery.
- [ ] **Notification types**: Enable/disable notifications for interactions (e.g., new comment, like, album favorited).

## ALL USERS - Authentication

- [x] **Login page**: Sign in with email and password.
- [x] **Register page**: Sign up with username, email and password.
- [x] **Sign out**: End session.
- [x] **Navigate auth**: Switch between login and register windows.
- [x] **Access control**: Restrict features to authenticated users (regular roles).
- [x] **Blocked account notice**: Show suspension notice and contact admin option.
- [x] **Unsigned user limits**: Allow browsing but with limited interactions (e.g., view-only top photos).

## ADMIN USER - Profile

- [ ] **Contacts**: Can view contact messages sent by users and mark them as resolved.
  - Should be able to mark as resolved and delete the message from the list of contacts
- [ ] **Reporting**: View reports of inappropriate content and take action (e.g., remove content, block user).
  - Should be able to mark as resolved and delete the report from the list of reports.
  - Mark as resolved means that the admin has taken action on the report and it is no longer pending review. This could involve removing the reported content, blocking the offending user, or taking other appropriate measures based on the nature of the report. Once marked as resolved, the report should be removed from the list of active reports to keep the admin dashboard organized and focused on unresolved issues.

## ALL USERS - Profile

- [X] **Change Avatar**: User can upload a new profile picture (accept jpg/png, max 2MB).
- [X] **Change password**: User can change account password.
- [ ] **Albums**: Create and manage photo albums.
- [X] **Empty State** - No Albums: Show empty state when user has no albums.
- [ ] **List albums**: Show user's albums.
- [ ] **Edit album**: Rename and delete own albums.
- [ ] **Add photo to Album**: Upload photo with short description (max 150 chars), publish date (auto), category, and image file (accept jpg/png, max 5MB) to an album. Users can only add photos to their own albums.
- [X] **Feature Photos** : Should display top 3 photos in the user profile based on the highest interactions similar to the catalog when filtering by highest commented, most liked or highest rated. This section should be prominently displayed in the user profile to showcase the user's most popular photos.

## VISITORS - Profile

- [X] **Follow/Unfollow Users**: Allow user to follow or unfollow other users trough there profile page.
- [ ] **View Albuns**: Allow users to view the albums of other users from their profile page.
- [X] **Unsigned User Profile Access**: Unsigned users can view profiles but cannot follow/unfollow or see albums. Can only see feature photos of the user profile.


## ALL USERS - FAVORITES ALBUNS

- [ ] **List favorite albuns**: Show the list of the user's favorite albuns with album details (name, author, category) and interactions: navigate to album photos, preview photos, like photos, view comments, rate photos, report photos.
- [X] **Empty state — no favorite albuns**: Display an empty state when the user has no favorite albuns.
- [ ] **Empty state — selected album has no photos**: When a favorite album is selected but contains no photos, display an empty state informing the user that there are no photos in this album.
- [ ] **Empty state — selected album removed by owner**: If a selected favorite album is no longer available because the owner removed it, show an empty state explaining the album was removed and offer an option to remove it from favorites.
- [x] **Remove favorite album**: Allow the user to remove a single album from their favorites list.
- [x] **Add favorite album**: Allow the user to add an album to their favorites list from the album view!

## ALL USERS (NOT UNSIGNED USERS) - Photo Content & Albums (Catalog - Explore)

- [x] **Gallery**: Display a gallery of photos of albums (catalog - Explore)
- [x] **Gallery Treeview**: Show albums in a treeview structure with album name, author and category.
- [x] **Pagination**: Implement pagination for photo galleries to improve load times and user experience. Should render 10 photos per page with navigation controls to move between pages.
- [x] **Photo Preview Card**: Show selected photo with preview details (author(avatar, username), nlikes, nComments, rating)
- [x] **Photo Preview Navigation**: Allow users to navigate in the photo preview card to see the next/previous photo in the treeview catalog.
- [x] **Treeview Selection**: Allow users to select a photo from the treeview to view its details in the photo preview card.
- [x] **Buttons on photo preview**: Add Like, View details, View comments, View album, Delete Photo and Report photo buttons on photo preview.
- [x] **Photo Detail View**: Access to the photo detail views window.
- [x] **Comments View**: Access to the comments view window.
- [x] **Album View**: Access to the album photo belongs to view window.
- [x] **Author View**: Access to the author profile view window. (only for other users, not for the photo owner)
- [x] **Report Photo View Dialog**: Access to the report dialog view window to report a photo.
- [x] **Delete Photo**: Allow users to delete their own photos from the catalog. (Only visible to the photo owner)
- [x] **Admin Delete Photo**: Allow admins to delete any photo from the catalog. (Visible to admins on all photos)
- [x] **Report Photo Access** : Allow users to report any photo from the catalog. (Visible to all users except unsigned users, and the photo owner). Admin cannot be reported. Admin can´t report photos since they are responsible for moderating content.
- [x] **Full Evaluations for Rating System**: The user should be able to see the number of ratings and be updated real-time when they rate a photo.
- [x] **Empty state No Photos**: Show empty state when no photos in the catalog for filters applied or no photos at all.
- [x] **Empty state photo preview**: Show empty state when there is no photo selected in the treeview.

## UNSIGNED USERS - Photo Content & Albums (Catalog - Explore)

- [x] **Limited Access**: Can view only the Top 5 photos and seeing the author profile (avatar and username) but cannot interact (like, see details, see comments, see album, report photo, delete photo) and cannot filter or sort photos.
- [x] **Message for unsigned users**: Show a message the they need the admin approval to interact with the photos and albums. The message should be displayed prominently on the catalog page.

## ALL USERS - Filtering & Sorting (Catalog - Explore)

- [x] **Filter by user**: Search photos by author.
- [x] **Filter by category**: Select category filter.
- [x] **Sort by views/likes/date/rate**: Allow sorting catalog by popularity or recency.
  - Default sorting should be by publish date (newest first).
  - Sorting options should include: "Most Recent", "Most Liked", "Highest Rated", "Most Commented".

## ALL USERS - Interaction (Catalog - Explore)

- [x] **Likes**: Users can like or unlike photos, with like count displayed on photo preview and detail view.
- [x] **Rating**: Allow users to rate photos (1-5 stars) and show average rating on photo preview and detail view.
- [x] **Rating System**: Implement a rating system where users can rate photos on a scale of 1 to 5 stars. The average rating should be displayed on the photo preview card and the photo detail view. Users should be able to update their rating, and the average rating should reflect any changes made by users.
- [x] **Hoover and Select Rating**: When a user hovers over the rating stars, they should be able to see the rating options and select their desired rating. Once a rating is selected, it should be submitted and the average rating should be updated accordingly.

## ALL USERS - Comments

- [x] **Add comment**: Users can add comments to photos.
- [x] **View comments**: Users can view comments on photos.
- [x] **Delete comment**: Users can delete their own comments. Admin can delete any comment. (Delete button only visible to comment owner and admins)
- [x] **Admin Delete comment**: Allow admins to delete any comment from the photo detail view. (Visible to admins on all comments)
- [x] **Empty state No Comments**: Show empty state when no comments on the photo.
- [x] **Comment details**: Show comment details (author(avatar, username), content, timestamp) on the photo detail view and comments view.
- [x] **Timestamp format**: Display comment timestamps in a human-readable format (e.g., "2 hours ago", "Yesterday", "3 days ago") instead of raw date-time values. It can´t be the created_at timestamp because when the comment is edited, the created_at timestamp is updated to the edit time. So we need to have a separate field for the original creation time of the comment that does not change when the comment is edited. This way, we can display the correct "time ago" format based on the original creation time of the comment, even if it has been edited.
- [x] **Pagination for comments**: Implement pagination for comments view to improve load times and user experience. Should render 5 comments per page with navigation controls to move between pages.

## ALL USERS - See Album Details

- [x] **List album photos** : Display the photos of the album in a listbox widget with the name of the photo only!
- [x] **Name of the Photo**: Should be displayed with the generic following format: "Photo {photo_id} — {first 30 characters of the description}…" (em-dash separator; description truncated to 30 characters with an ellipsis if longer).
- [x] **Empty state No Photos**: Show empty state when no photos in the album!
- [x] **Default State of the Listbox**: By default it shows the selected photo in the catalog!
- [x] **Select photo from the listbox**: When a user selects a photo from the listbox, the selected photo should be displayed in the photo preview card with its details ( nlikes, nComments, rating) and interactions (like, view details, view comments, delete photo or report photo buttons).
- [x] **Album Header**: Display only the album name. Author info is already shown in the photo preview panel metadata, making it redundant in the header.

## ALL USERS - See Photo Details

- [x] **Photo details**: Show photo details (author(avatar, username), description, category, nlikes, nComments, rating) on the photo detail view.
- [x] **View Comments from Photo Detail View**: Allow users to access the comments view directly from the photo detail view by clicking a "View Comments" button. This button should be prominently displayed on the photo detail view, and when clicked, it should open the comments view for that specific photo, allowing users to read and interact with the comments without having to navigate back to the catalog or photo preview.
- [x] **Report Photo from Photo Detail View** : Allow users to report a photo directly from the photo detail view by clicking a "Report Photo" button.

## ALL USERS - Notifications

- [ ] **Notification system**: Users receive notifications for interactions (e.g., new comment, like, album favorited).
  - Receives notifications when:
    - A user comments on their photo.
    - A user likes their photo.
    - A user adds their album to favorites.
    - New follower.
    - Comment or photo deleted by admin (notify with a reason provided by the removed content)
  - Notification details should include:
    - Type of interaction (e.g., comment, like, favorite).
    - User who performed the interaction (e.g., username and avatar).
    - Timestamp of the interaction.
  - Users should be able to view their notifications in a dedicated notifications page or dropdown menu.
  - Users should have the option to mark notifications as read or delete them from their notification list.

## Blocked Users

- [x] **Contact Admin**: Blocked users can contact admin to resolve issues.
- [x] **Blocked account notice**: Show suspension notice and contact admin option.
- [ ] **Display reason for block**: When a user is blocked, display the reason for the block (e.g., "Inappropriate content", "Spam", "Harassment") and the comment or photo reported that led to the block. This information should be visible on the blocked account notice page to provide transparency and help the user understand why they were blocked.

## ALL USERS - Reporting & Moderation

- [x] **Report content**: Users can report inappropriate photos or comments, providing a reason for the report ( e.g., "Inappropriate content", "Spam", "Harassment"). Reported content should be flagged for admin review. If selected other, a text input should appear to provide more details about the report. This information should be included in the report sent to the admin for review.
